Last Sunset in Antananarivo
Life in Antananarivo presents its challenges, including frequent water shortages, power cuts, and notorious traffic. However, the city also offers rewards: delicious fresh food and breathtaking sunsets 😍

I'm back in France now and I'm incredibly grateful to live in such a developed country. I'm committed to spending time figuring out how I can contribute to Madagascar's improvement, especially in essential services like water and electricity.

Ankadinandriana My Ancestors' Land
This is where my father's maternal family comes from. It's a typical rural village not too far from the capital city, Antananarivo, but with dirt roads that are almost unusable when it rains!
I definitely love the color red/orange of the soil everywhere 🤩

Nosy Iranja: the postcard island
Nosy Iranja is a bit far, around 1.5 hours from Nosy Be, but it's definitely a must do  with its beautiful long beaches of white coral sand 🤩

Nosy Sakatia: the turtle island
This is the first place I've been to with so many huge sea turtles feeding underwater 🤯. I definitely need to buy a waterproof camera to capture that amazing sight!
There are also gorgeous beaches on Sakatia 🤩.

Nosy Komba: the lemur island
Nosy Komba is a small island renowned for its close encounters with lemurs. The maki macacos are accustomed to being hand-fed bananas by tourists under the watchful eye of a local guide. The island is also known for its exceptional vanilla.

Sunset in Nosy Be

Madagascar South West Road Trip
Road trips in Madagascar are one of my favorite things: stunning landscapes and simple yet delicious roadside food. 🤩 
The only downside is that a significant portion of the roads is in poor condition. I highly recommend renting a 4x4 and hiring an experienced driver. 👌🏾

Lemurs of the Kirindy Forest 🤩🤩🤩
The Kirindy Forest is located in western Madagascar, two hours away from Morondava. It's home to six lemur species, and I was lucky enough to spot five of them! I even managed to capture some great photos of three. 🙌🏾

The fossa: Madagascar's top predator 😽😽😽
It's the first time I've encountered this endemic Madagascar animal in the wild! 🤯 
It acts like a big cat but isn't one, being more closely related to the mongoose. Though supposedly dangerous, this one seems used to humans, as it apparently often comes to greet lodge guests. 😅

Tsingy de Bemaraha
I finally made it to one of Madagascar's most popular tourist destinations: the very remote Tsingy of Bemaraha 🤩

My 77 years old parents and my 8 and 12 years old nephews made it too 🔥💪🏾

Lemurs are also living a great life in this park 😊
